# CI/CD Pipeline Patterns

## Overview

Our CI/CD pipeline uses Coolify with GitHub App integration for automated deployments.

## Deployment Configuration

### 1. Coolify GitHub App Setup

```yaml
# Coolify Integration Configuration
coolify:
  type: 'github-app'
  integration:
    name: '@Coolify'
    scope: 'private'
    repository_type: 'Private Repository (with GitHub App)'
    auto_deploy: true
    features:
      - Automatic commit deployments
      - Pull request preview environments
      - Branch protection rules
      - Deployment status updates
      - Automatic cleanup
      - Real-time monitoring

  # Environment Configuration
  environments:
    production:
      branch: main
      domain: ${PRODUCTION_DOMAIN}
      auto_deploy: false
      requires_approval: true
      force_https: true
      health_check: true

    staging:
      branch: develop
      domain: ${STAGING_DOMAIN}
      auto_deploy: true
      requires_approval: false
      preview_deployments: true
      force_https: true
      health_check: true

  # Preview Deployments
  preview:
    enabled: true
    url_template: '{{pr_id}}.{{domain}}'
    auto_deploy: true
    cleanup_on_close: true

  # Build Configuration
  build:
    pack: 'nixpacks'
    command: 'pnpm build'
    static_site: true
    cache: true
```

